H0.text: Skull is the bone structure that limits the space within which the telencephalon enlarges and grows into the cranial cavity.

H1.text: Skeleton is the bone structure within which the telencephalon is limited as it enlarges and grows into the cranial cavity.

H2.text: Spine is the bone structure that limits the space into which the telencephalon enlarges and grows within the cranial cavity.

H3.text: Chest is the bone structure that limits the space within which the telencephalon enlarges and grows into the cranial cavity.

A4.text: The neurocranium (or braincase) forms the protective cranial cavity that surrounds and houses the brain and brainstem.

A5.text: The skull, or cranium, is typically a bony enclosure around the brain of a vertebrate.
